{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/2019/03/26/blender-tutorial-12-camera-rendering/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about camera and rendering.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/2019/03/25/blender-tutorial-11-light-part-2/\">previous post of the series \"Blender tutorial\"</a> we talked\nabout light in Blender. In this post we will talk about camera and rendering. Let's start from camera.<br>\nIf we select a camera, we can access its properties from the specific camera tab in the properties panel. Here we have a\nsection called \"Display\", that let us customize how we see the camera in the viewport (limits, names and so on). Then we\nhave a \"Lens\" section, where we can choose the type of the camera:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>orthogonal</li>\n<li>perspective</li>\n<li>panoramic</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For the perspective camera we can change:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the focal length</li>\n<li>the shift, so as the word say we can change the shift of the camera from its center</li>\n<li>the clipping, the start end distance between which the object see by the camera will be rendered.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For the orthographic camera the most important parameter is the orthographic scale, that represent the maximum\ndimension (in scene units) of the portion of space captured from the camera.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/c58a3/blender-camera-options.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Camera options\"\n        title=\"Camera options\"\n        src=\"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/0470c/blender-camera-options.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/6c669/blender-camera-options.jpg 285w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/882a4/blender-camera-options.jpg 570w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/0470c/blender-camera-options.jpg 1140w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/c58a3/blender-camera-options.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Camera options</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>We can place cameras manually or we can use constraints. We can create a constraint by clicking the specific constraint\ntab (the one with the chain as icon) in the properties panel of the camera and add a new constraint. We can use for\nexample a Damped Track and correlate the movement of our camera to the position of an object we select as the one to be\ntracked.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/c58a3/blender-camera-constraints.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Camera constraints\"\n        title=\"Camera constraints\"\n        src=\"/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/0470c/blender-camera-constraints.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/6c669/blender-camera-constraints.jpg 285w,\n/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/882a4/blender-camera-constraints.jpg 570w,\n/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/0470c/blender-camera-constraints.jpg 1140w,\n/static/d7682d826c06c5dcb9e3dfed69ce5c33/c58a3/blender-camera-constraints.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Camera constraints</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>For what concerns rendering, we have the possibility to control it in the properties panel under the render tab (the one\nwith the camera). For example we can customize where the render will happen. By default the render will show the result\nin the image editor, but we can change it by selecting one of the available option in the list. We can change the\ndimensions of the render result in terms of width/height but also in terms of FPS. We will see why this parameter is\nimportant in a future post about <strong>animations</strong>. We can also customize the algorithm used for anti aliasing. Very\nimportant, we can also customize the shading option (as we already see in a previous post about shadows), the\nperformance (for example by adjusting the number of thread that Blender will be allowed to use), and the format of final\noutput of the rendering.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/c58a3/blender-render-option.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Rendering option\"\n        title=\"Rendering option\"\n        src=\"/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/0470c/blender-render-option.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/6c669/blender-render-option.jpg 285w,\n/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/882a4/blender-render-option.jpg 570w,\n/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/0470c/blender-render-option.jpg 1140w,\n/static/6547e789f2c77502a3ea21c455e0f357/c58a3/blender-render-option.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Rendering option</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>As we said before in Blender it is possible to render animation. We will go through all the details about animation in a\nfuture post. For now we can see how to achieve cool rendering effects, for example motion blur. The motion blur is an\neffect you have when an object is moving in the length of the exposure of the camera. We can achieve this effect by\nactivating it in the rendering properties and setting the number of motion sample we want. We can also modify the\nshutter to change the final result of the motion blur (the default value for samples is 1, and we need to modify it\nbecause with the value of 1 we will have no motion blur).</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/c58a3/blender-motion-blur.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.94736842105264%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add motion blur\"\n        title=\"Add motion blur\"\n        src=\"/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/0470c/blender-motion-blur.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/6c669/blender-motion-blur.jpg 285w,\n/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/882a4/blender-motion-blur.jpg 570w,\n/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/0470c/blender-motion-blur.jpg 1140w,\n/static/18b42c3ef524c22ae32e1bf1aae657ad/c58a3/blender-motion-blur.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add motion blur</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>One last effect we can achieve with the Blender render is depth of field. This effect simulate the fact that only a part\nof the scene is in focus, based on the focal distance from the camera. To setup the depth of field in our scene, first\nof all we have to activate it by increasing the distance option in the depth of field section of the camera properties.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.298245614035096%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add blender depth of field\"\n        title=\"Add blender depth of field\"\n        src=\"/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/6c669/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/882a4/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/4c0c6978c4dfcff690b0854a1cf04350/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add blender depth of field</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After that we have to switch to the node editor, add a defocus filter, and connect the render image and depth to the\nfilter, and again the image to the composite final result.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.298245614035096%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Activate the node editor\"\n        title=\"Activate the node editor\"\n        src=\"/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/6c669/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg 285w,\n/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/882a4/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg 570w,\n/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg 1140w,\n/static/d1c5a1a397f251e8cd8adbb7d3f6511f/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-2.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Activate the node editor</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.298245614035096%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Select the blur filter\"\n        title=\"Select the blur filter\"\n        src=\"/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/6c669/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg 285w,\n/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/882a4/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg 570w,\n/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg 1140w,\n/static/82cc4f39a8ae60fdc0b9a145db9093f8/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-3.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Select the blur filter</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.298245614035096%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Setup defocus\"\n        title=\"Setup defocus\"\n        src=\"/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/6c669/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg 285w,\n/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/882a4/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg 570w,\n/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg 1140w,\n/static/8a85dbab0f3a41bf34fc66c06cbe419a/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-4.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Setup defocus</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.89473684210527%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The depth of field final result\"\n        title=\"The depth of field final result\"\n        src=\"/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/6c669/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg 285w,\n/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/882a4/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg 570w,\n/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/0470c/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg 1140w,\n/static/c18b8773852c13ffbbb8054e9ba19c3e/c58a3/blender-depth-of-field-5.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The depth of field final result</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>That's all for camera and rendering. In the next post we will talk about animation.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Blender tutorial: camera and rendering","comments":true,"authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"date":"26 Mar 2019","description":"In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about camera and rendering.","math":false,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/f36b9/blender-camera-options.jpg","srcSet":"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/4dbc9/blender-camera-options.jpg 750w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/f3163/blender-camera-options.jpg 1080w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/23c2c/blender-camera-options.jpg 1366w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/f36b9/blender-camera-options.jpg 1500w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/6b595/blender-camera-options.webp 750w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/88654/blender-camera-options.webp 1080w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/164a2/blender-camera-options.webp 1366w,\n/static/6574900ae4932156af28887696429e43/5f4ea/blender-camera-options.webp 1500w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.63}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/2019/03/26/blender-tutorial-12-camera-rendering/","readingTime":{"text":"4 min read"}}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Fabrizio Duroni"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2019/03/26/blender-tutorial-12-camera-rendering/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3076394108","3309278767","3736063423","4159577854"]}